Glucocorticoids Glucocorticoids

  • lipoprotein a: A lipoprotein present on LDL particles which increases atherogenicity. It is NOT influenced by diet; only genetically determined. Once in a life time check is enough to assess levels and ASCVD risk. Levels are not reduced by statins. No evidence for starting Lp(a) lowering PCSK9i drugs for primary prevention.

  • Benefit of statins is a class effect: no one statin is more effective than the others.

  • High intensity therapy: > 50% reduction in LDL-c

  • Moderate: 30 to 49% reduction;

  • Low intensity : <30% reduction


Side effects of statin therapy
  • Overall incidence is low (<2%)
  • Significant odds ratios have been found for
    • liver enzyme elevation - true hepatotoxicity, liver failure are very rare.
    • Muscle related symptoms
    • Rhabdomyolysis / myositis / myopathy is a known side effect (but rare)
    • They can cause new onset diabetes.
    • Reversible proteinuria of tubular origin. (not a big deal)
